{
  "stem": "3952.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I-- I-- I'm very surprised.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is the one I should have told the first, and I'm surprised that I forgot all about it while I was talking about Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is what it does to you when you-- when you talk about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When you relive it, you-- you get so excited that you don't know what exactly to talk about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember an incident where suddenly somebody yelled out, look, look!",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we turned around, and we saw, near the ladies, where the bath was, some ladies came out, and one of them had a baby in her arms.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one of the SS men went to her and took the lady, grabbed the lady-- the baby out of her-- of the lady's hands and threw the baby up in the air.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And like four-- four SS men shot their revolvers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They shot through the baby to see who can shoot her more times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they laughed, and they enjoyed themselves.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This was like, what shall I say, 200 feet away from us, maybe 250 feet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it was a very clear picture, very clearly so.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were still fresh from home, and I-- I couldn't believe that something like this is happening.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So somebody said, yeah, it must have been something else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's not the baby.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So immediate-- and you wanted to believe that, that it was not the baby.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and I recall an instant after liberation, when I was with-- with-- in an American field hospital, one of the male nurses, a guy by the name of Larry McCormick, from New Jersey somewhere, that's all I remember about him.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He came back from the crematorium, and he said, Izchak, I have taken photographs, but I can't believe it's true.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
